00:11:14,341 --> 00:11:17,943
   narrator: a cylinder stove   
     is designed for campers    

185
00:11:17,945 --> 00:11:19,945
            who like            
    their creature comforts.    

186
00:11:19,947 --> 00:11:23,282
       just pitch the tent      
  and set up the stove inside.  

187
00:11:23,284 --> 00:11:26,351
 it keeps things warm and toasty
     for most of the night.     

188
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:30,288
  it also has a cooking surface 
     and a tank at the side     

189
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:33,225
      to provide hot water      
          for washing.          

190
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:40,499
    no need to huddle around    
    a campfire to stay warm.    

191
00:11:40,501 --> 00:11:42,501
        a cylinder stove        
       can take the chill       

192
00:11:42,503 --> 00:11:44,636
             out of             
   the wilderness experience.   

193
00:11:44,638 --> 00:11:47,339
      the cylindrical shape     
   means it can take the heat.  

194
00:11:47,341 --> 00:11:50,708
   it will expand and contract  
   with the temperature change  

195
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:53,979
       and still maintain       
      it's original shape.      

196
00:11:53,981 --> 00:11:58,182
 the cylindrical firebox starts 
   with a flat sheet of steel.  

197
00:11:58,184 --> 00:12:00,718
        a worker feeds it       
   through a roller repeatedly  

198
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,454
        until it reaches        
       the desired shape.       

199
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:09,327
    then a plasma cutter cuts   
  an opening for the stove door 

200
00:12:09,329 --> 00:12:12,931
   in another sheet of steel,   
  following a pattern overhead. 

201
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:16,401
        the plasma cutter       
works by sending an electric arc

202
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:19,638
     through compressed air,    
 and the result is a clean cut. 

203
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:26,545
  he now places the stove body  
      on the door framework     

204
00:12:26,547 --> 00:12:29,147
     and clamps the assembly    
        in a special jig        

205
00:12:29,149 --> 00:12:33,819
    to secure it as he welds    
    the two parts together.     

206
00:12:33,821 --> 00:12:37,222
         he then places         
 the backplate on the workbench 

207
00:12:37,224 --> 00:12:40,359
   and positions the other end  
     of the cylinder on it.     

208
00:12:40,361 --> 00:12:43,695
      he clamps them there      
    and welds them together.    

209
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,766
    using the plasma cutter,    

210
00:12:47,768 --> 00:12:50,302
   he trims the front and back  
          of the stove.         

211
00:12:50,304 --> 00:12:53,971
          the trimming          
     rounds the ends nicely.    

212
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:58,377
 from three flat sheets of steel
    to a cylindrical firebox,   

213
00:12:58,379 --> 00:13:02,381
       the transformation       
 has taken less than 10 minutes.

214
00:13:02,383 --> 00:13:05,584
    the welder now reinforces   
 the underside of the stove top 

215
