226
00:13:46,292 --> 00:13:47,959
          creating tabs         
      to keep the stovepipe     

227
00:13:47,961 --> 00:13:52,230
 from sliding into the firebox. 

228
00:13:52,232 --> 00:13:53,832
     he's now ready to join     

229
00:13:53,834 --> 00:13:56,435
     the cylindrical firebox    
        to the stove top.       

230
00:13:56,437 --> 00:14:00,272
    he locks them in position   
 and welds the entire assembly. 

231
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:04,642
     this final welded seam     
         seals the stove        

232
00:14:04,644 --> 00:14:06,712
         for an airtight        
     and long-lasting burn.     

233
00:14:09,917 --> 00:14:13,785
 next he positions leg fittings 
    on the belly of the stove   

234
00:14:13,787 --> 00:14:17,322
  using a sawhorse-style tool.  

235
00:14:17,324 --> 00:14:20,458
   once he welds the fittings   
          to the stove,         

236
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:22,027
      he removes the tool.      

237
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:27,599
         then it's over         
to a computerized plasma cutter.

238
00:14:27,601 --> 00:14:31,670
      it cuts damper holes      
       in the stove door.       

239
00:14:31,672 --> 00:14:33,672
      damper holes are used     
   to regulate the flow of air  

240
00:14:33,674 --> 00:14:34,773
          to the fire.          

241
00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:40,679
they also install a baffle plate
  on the back of the stove door 

242
00:14:40,681 --> 00:14:43,081
 to keep sparks from flying out 
         into the tent.         

243
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:49,487
  the worker attaches the door  
   to the stove with a hinge.   

244
00:14:49,489 --> 00:14:55,227
     he tests it to confirm     
that it opens and closes easily.

245
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:57,963
  another worker now roles pipe 
        for the chimney,        

246
00:14:57,965 --> 00:15:00,832
     using galvanized steel     
    because it doesn't rust.    

247
00:15:00,834 --> 00:15:03,935
     he interlocks the seam     
        and flattens it.        

248
00:15:03,937 --> 00:15:05,504
       he crimps the ends       

249
00:15:05,506 --> 00:15:09,173
       to connect the pipe      
  to the other pieces of pipe.  

250
00:15:09,175 --> 00:15:11,643
      there are five pieces     
      of stovepipe in all,      

251
00:15:11,645 --> 00:15:14,846
and they can be stacked together
         for transport.         

252
00:15:14,848 --> 00:15:17,315
   with the latch now attached  
       to the stove door,       

253
00:15:17,317 --> 00:15:21,319
   he sprays black stove paint  
  onto the cylindrical firebox. 

254
00:15:21,321 --> 00:15:24,856
          the paint job         
      will prevent rusting.     

255
00:15:24,858 --> 00:15:27,992
        finally he rivets       
   a brass manufacturer's tag   

256
00:15:27,994 --> 00:15:29,461
      onto the stove front.     

257
00:15:29,463 --> 00:15:31,530
  now it's time to pack it up.  

258
00:15:31,532 --> 00:15:35,000
from the grate to the water tank
        to the stovepipe,       

259
00:15:35,002 --> 00:15:38,203
    everything can be stowed    
      inside the fire box,      

260
00:15:38,205 --> 00:15:40,271
 making it completely portable. 

261
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:44,008
assembly in the tent should take
      about five minutes --     

262
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:46,745
           a small job          
    for a long-lasting burn.    

263
00:15:46,747 --> 00:15:48,547
   the biggest cylinder stoves  

264
00:15:48,549 --> 00:15:52,083
   are designed to hold a fire  
      for an entire night.      

265
00:15:52,085 --> 00:15:53,351
   and with the proper setup,   

266
00:15:53,353 --> 00:15:56,488
      campers should sleep      
         safe and sound.        

267
00:15:56,490 --> 00:16:00,825
       installing a piece       
    of heat-resistant rubber    

268
00:16:00,827 --> 00:16:03,294
        protects the tent       
      around the stovepipe.     

269
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:06,364
         then it's time         
  to hunker down for the night  

270
00:16:06,366 --> 00:16:09,201
    and enjoy a little warmth   
       in the wilderness.       

271
00:16:25,185 --> 00:16:28,453
     narrator: spun concrete    
     light poles tower above    

272
00:16:28,455 --> 00:16:31,322
      our towns and cities,     
        lighting the way.       

273
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:33,058
        they're actually        
        hollow structures       

274
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:35,994
      with wiring or cable      
    snaked through the cores.   

275
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:39,064
       the concrete walls       
    are reinforced by steel.    

276
00:16:39,066 --> 00:16:41,199
         yet these poles        
       are flexible enough      

277
00:16:41,201 --> 00:16:43,935
      to bend with the wind     
         and snap back.         

278
00:16:46,873 --> 00:16:50,207
   when it comes to lampposts,  
      the higher the light,     

279
00:16:50,209 --> 00:16:52,677
           the greater          
      the area illuminated.     

280
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:56,814
    some concrete light poles   
  are over three stories high.  

281
00:16:56,816 --> 00:16:59,016
    they start with a tenon,    

282
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:02,219
 the part of the pole framework 
 that anchors the light fixture.

283
00:17:02,221 --> 00:17:03,888
    they place two in a mold    

284
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,958
     because they're making     
    two light poles at once.    

285
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,628
  a worker strings four thick,  
          steel strands         

286
00:17:09,630 --> 00:17:12,030
  from one end of the long mold 
          to the other,         

287
00:17:12,032 --> 00:17:14,231
         threading them         
       through the tenons       

288
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,900
    and through spiral wire.    

289
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:19,637
   this establishes the basic   
framework of the concrete poles.

290
00:17:19,639 --> 00:17:22,040
         another worker         
       installs zinc boxes      

291
00:17:22,042 --> 00:17:23,908
   for electrical connections.  

292
00:17:23,910 --> 00:17:26,711
           he caps it           
   with a block of rigid foam   

293
00:17:26,713 --> 00:17:29,914
          to protect it         
  when the concrete is poured.  

294
00:17:29,916 --> 00:17:32,850
         the next worker        
      attaches a stress gun     

295
00:17:32,852 --> 00:17:35,987
      to chucks that secure     
       the steel strands.       

296
00:17:35,989 --> 00:17:38,189
    the gun pulls the strands   
           one by one           

297
00:17:38,191 --> 00:17:40,058
     to a specific tension,     

298
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:42,994
        and they stretch        
       like rubber bands.       

299
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:46,464
        they'll be pulled       
       even tighter later.      

300
00:17:46,466 --> 00:17:51,736
 every yard or so, he attaches  
 stay rings for extra rigidity. 

301
00:17:51,738 --> 00:17:56,308
      he ties them in place     
    with plastic-coated wire.   

302
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:02,213
         another worker         
    stretches the spiral wire   

303
00:18:02,215 --> 00:18:04,882
    around the steel strands    
           and tenons           

304
00:18:04,884 --> 00:18:08,153
    to round out the skeleton   
       of the light poles.      

305
00:18:08,155 --> 00:18:11,156
         the spiral wire        
     will also stop the pole    

306
00:18:11,158 --> 00:18:15,426
     from twisting too much     
         in high winds.         

307
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:18,563
        a crane transfers       
     the long and hefty mold    

308
00:18:18,565 --> 00:18:24,301
  over to the next station and  
 lowers it onto several stands. 

309
00:18:24,303 --> 00:18:27,638
a hopper now swings into action,
       guided by workers.       

310
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:30,241
        it's a traveling        
       concrete dispenser.      

311
00:18:30,243 --> 00:18:32,443
     as it moves on a track,    
           it funnels           

312
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:35,380
    specially mixed concrete    
         into the mold.         

313
00:18:35,382 --> 00:18:37,515
          the concrete          
     has been made to order,    

314
00:18:37,517 --> 00:18:40,719
  with the customer specifying  
      its color, strength,      

315
00:18:40,721 --> 00:18:44,389
      and other qualities.      

316
00:18:44,391 --> 00:18:47,459
      the concrete also has     
     a low moisture content.    

317
00:18:47,461 --> 00:18:50,729
          this makes it         
     the consistency of clay    

318
00:18:50,731 --> 00:18:53,331
     and therefore formable.    

319
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,199
  as the concrete is dispensed, 

320
00:18:55,201 --> 00:18:59,737
     workers pack it around     
the light pole's steel skeleton.

321
00:18:59,739 --> 00:19:02,874
         using trowels,         
     they scoop up overflow     

322
00:19:02,876 --> 00:19:05,610
     and smooth the surface     
      of the wet concrete.      

323
00:19:05,612 --> 00:19:09,214
    one worker then cleans up   
        the outer flanges       

324
00:19:09,216 --> 00:19:12,016
           and applies          
      a nonstick substance.     

325
00:19:12,018 --> 00:19:15,486
   a crane moves the top half   
   of the mold into position    

326
00:19:15,488 --> 00:19:19,023
       and lowers it onto       
the concrete-filled bottom part.

327
00:19:19,025 --> 00:19:22,694
  the team bolts the two parts  
  of the mold tightly together  

328
00:19:22,696 --> 00:19:24,629
  using pneumatic impact tools. 

329
00:19:24,631 --> 00:19:28,566
 they now pull the steel strands
     to their final tension,    

330
00:19:28,568 --> 00:19:30,435
   stretching them so tightly   

331
00:19:30,437 --> 00:19:33,838
 that they compress the concrete
        once it hardens.        

332
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:37,108
    concrete is much stronger   
   when it's being compressed.  

333
00:19:38,712 --> 00:19:41,646
      the mold is now ready     
    for the spinning machine.   

334
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:44,648
        it's essentially        
   a series of railway wheels.  

335
00:19:44,650 --> 00:19:46,984
         a crane lowers         
    the mold's running rings    

336
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:48,986
 into the grooves of the wheels,

337
00:19:48,988 --> 00:19:51,389
     and then they crank up     
           the speed.           

338
00:19:51,391 --> 00:19:55,660
  the wheels turn at 500 rpms,  
    and the centrifugal force   

339
00:19:55,662 --> 00:19:59,463
 causes the concrete to migrate 
    to the wall of the mold.    

340
00:19:59,465 --> 00:20:03,535
   the result is a hollow pole  
   with dense, concrete walls.  

341
00:20:05,138 --> 00:20:07,605
     transferred to a kiln,     
    the concrete steam-cures    

342
00:20:07,607 --> 00:20:10,708
           in the mold          
      for about five hours.     

343
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:14,545
    the concrete light poles    
  are ready for the big reveal. 

344
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:19,216
       they open the mold       
       and roll them out.       

345
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:22,353
  at this point, the two poles  
       are still attached.      

346
00:20:22,355 --> 00:20:26,357
  they examine them for flaws,  
 and then they'll separate them.

347
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:30,561
        all they need now       
       is some buffing up.      

348
00:20:30,563 --> 00:20:34,098
        here, they polish       
   a different octagonal pole   

349
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:36,067
     to expose the pigments     
        in the concrete.        

350
00:20:39,773 --> 00:20:43,708
the different colored aggregates
  in this particular cement mix 

351
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:45,777
          give the pole         
     a mottled marble look.     

352
00:20:48,782 --> 00:20:53,317
an i.d. tag has also been molded
         into the cement        

353
00:20:53,319 --> 00:20:56,121
   with the manufacturing date  
 and the pole's height and mass.

354
00:20:58,724 --> 00:21:00,859
     they test just how far     
        they can take it        

355
00:21:00,861 --> 00:21:05,329
       to confirm the pole      
    meets industry standards.   

356
00:21:05,331 --> 00:21:08,399
      they spray a special      
 acrylic finish onto some poles.

357
00:21:08,401 --> 00:21:11,603
         graffiti can be        
   easily scrubbed off of it.   

358
00:21:14,007 --> 00:21:16,407
    even though it only takes   
        about 5 1/2 hours       

359
00:21:16,409 --> 00:21:19,210
         to manufacture         
     a concrete light pole,     

360
00:21:19,212 --> 00:21:21,713
 it should shine for many years.

